President Jacob Zuma has agreed to institute a judicial commission of inquiry into allegations of state capture.Zuma announced this a short while ago while responding to oral questions in the National Assembly.He says he will provide details in a few days."We have taken the decision to establish a judicial commission of inquiry...we are moving as fast as possible on this matter." Need to stay informed? Investors Monthly is a magazine published by Times Media, Media Division included in the Financial Mail on the last Thursday of the month.